latestIgtvVideos.caption:
No Pants? No Problem! Here’s our guide to matching your swimwear to your body type.

Swim Briefs: these traditionally look best with slender body types, but honestly if you feel good in them, wear them. You be you!

Swim Shorts: If you’re rocking the dad bod, don’t be shy - show off that thigh (with a higher cut short).

Square Cut Trunks: Muscular body types typically look best in these traditional swim shorts that cut straight across at the bottom.

Mid-Length Shorts: If you’re a bigger dude, rock something a bit longer so that it doesn’t look small on you. Look for shorts that land more than halfway down your thigh, but cut off well above your knees.

Still not sure? Hit the link in bio for more in this week’s DSC Magazine.

As March Madness® comes to a close, it’s time for our hugely beloved and massively popular Twitter handle to return from this Chin Guy to our own people here at DSC.

It was so nice to see how many of our followers and basketball fans understood and unequivocally loved this takeover.

We will miss you, Drew Timme’s Chin, and all the light you brought to us. May you smoothly return to your owner.

#NCAA #MarchMadness #DrewTimme

You know what they always say, “A mustached man and his smooth chin are soon digitally parted so that one can be a very good basketball player and the other can be weird on Twitter.” It’s getting to the point where this is being said TOO much.

If you’ve been on Twitter the last few days you might have seen that our account has been taken over by a familiar chin: Drew Timme’s chin! This will be familiar if you’ve been watching the b-ball tournament. Otherwise it’s probably confusing!

But then anyway, Drew Timme has such a smooth chin that it has the ability to glide right off his face and post gifs on Twitter, specifically to our account. It’s really fun and you should stop whatever you are doing right this second and go check it out.

How long will he be posting for? HOW LONG DO YOU HAVE? Or, like, until the end of the tournament? Sure. Something like that. 

Please go over to Twitter right now and follow us and like and share every single tweet we’ve ever tweeted especially the stuff with the chin but also every other tweet. Thanks!

#NCAA #NCAAM #MarchMadness #DrewTimme
